cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM

The paper presents a novel approach for image synthesis that combines both appearance and geometry spaces. This makes it likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) which are a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach in two tasks related to image manipulation and processing, which could also make it relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
